bug.short_desc: kernel module snd-hda-intel will not initialize sound card
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1281205 with kernel 4.4.14-200.fc22.x86_64
Description of problem:
After upgrading from FC22 to FC25, the sound of my laptop was not working any-more. I switched back to kernel 4.4.14-200.fc22.x86_64 and got my sound working again.
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable):
4.10.15-200.fc25.x86_64 & snd-hda-intel
How reproducible:
It is possibly very hardware dependent. On this laptop, the integrated sound is HDA Intel PCH, ALC269VC Analog
Actual results:
kernel module will not find pcm driver. Integrated sound will not play.
Expected results:
kernel module will find pcm driver and initialize the device.
Additional info:
alsa-info.txt.dkF2FtQtXq - with kernel 4.4.14-200.fc22.x86_64
after reboot I will add into comment the alsa-info for kernel 4.10.15-200
